<br>
How languages work was changed a couple patches back.  You used to be able to get only 1 point per hour unless you zoned.  Now that limit's been removed.  You also used to have to be grouped to learn.  I'm pretty sure that's changed also, and you can learn just by having people talk near you.<br>
<br>
To learn in a group, sit down, switch to the language you're teaching, and keep talking in group.  (Make a button to say multiple lines with one touch of a button ... much easier.  Also, don't make the lines too long, as spamming really long lines can be kinda laggy.)  With the new UI, I recommend opening a new chat window and filtering all group say to this window.  Then it can scroll happily away in that window, and you'll still be able to see all your tells, channels, etc. without them zooming off the screen.<br>
<br>
You will see messages appear saying your skill in languages has improved.  After 100 of these, congrats, you are a master.  However, you will have to zone before the language appears in your languages list, and before your skill level is actually updated so you can understand that language.<br>
<br>
You don't need any points in a language in order to learn it.<br>
<br>
As you rise in ranks, your trainers will start offering you more and more languages to learn.  However, you can learn any language at any time from another player, whether or not your trainers think you're ready.<br>
<br>
Once you have reached a level in the language where you recognise what the language is ('very bad' I think, but might be wrong), you can understand custom emotes perfectly although /tells and /say will still be garbled.<br>
<br>
You need at least one point in a language to teach it.  You can teach it to one point higher than your skill level.  E.g. if you have 5 points of Barbarian, you can teach me 6 points.  Then we would have to zone, and then I could teach you to 7 points.  And so on.  If you have 100 points in Barbarian then we can just sit there until I'm a master also.  If you're learning from a master in a language and don't need to zone, it takes about 20 minutes or so to reach master.  The exact speed depends on your intelligence or wisdom (I believe that like trade skills, whichever is higher is used to calculate how fast you learn.)<br>
<br>
Many of the larger guilds often hold language faires where you can exchange languages, so you might look around some of the guild boards (many are found in the web ring at the bottom of the main page on this board, or look in the Guilds and Associations forum.)<br>
<br>
Note that with the new UI, languages are bugged, so you can't say /lang 5 to change to Dark Elf the way you could with the old UI.  Instead you need to right click on the main chat window bar, and navigate the languages menu with the mouse.  Hopefully this will be fixed soon.<br>
<br>
